That's a common issue with GitHub Pages! The problem is likely that GitHub Pages is applying some base styles or the CSS isn't loading correctly. Here's the fix:

Fix 1: Add CSS Reset for Footer

Add this to your CSS file (I've added it to the footer section):

```css
/* Footer - with explicit centering */
.footer-simple {
    margin-top: 40px;
    margin-bottom: 100px;
    padding: 20px 0;
    border-top: 2px solid var(--accent-light);
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    text-align: center !important; /* Force center alignment */
    clear: both;
    width: 100%; /* Ensure full width */
    display: block; /* Explicit block display */
}

.footer-simple p {
    margin: 0;
    line-height: 1.5;
    text-align: center !important; /* Force paragraph center */
    width: 100%;
}

.footer-simple strong {
    color: var(--accent-primary);
}

.footer-simple .copyright {
    color: var(--accent-primary);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    margin-left: 8px;
    display: inline-block; /* Keep inline with text */
}
```

Fix 2: Check Container Width

Make sure your container isn't restricting the footer. The footer is inside the container, so it should inherit the centering. Add this to ensure the container is properly centered:

```css
.container {
    width: 95%;
    max-width: 1600px;
    margin: 0 auto !important; /* Force auto margins */
    padding: 20px;
    display: block;
}
```

Fix 3: Add Inline Style as Backup

If the CSS still doesn't work on GitHub Pages, add a style tag in your HTML as a backup:

```html
<!-- Add this right before the footer -->
<style>
    /* GitHub Pages fallback */
    .footer-simple {
        text-align: center !important;
        margin-left: auto !important;
        margin-right: auto !important;
        width: 100% !important;
    }
    .footer-simple p {
        text-align: center !important;
    }
</style>

<!-- Simple footer -->
<footer class="footer-simple">
    <p>🌿 Developed by Jay Rowley <span class="copyright">© 2026</span></p>
</footer>
```

Fix 4: Check GitHub Pages Path

Sometimes GitHub Pages has issues with relative paths. Make sure your CSS link is correct:

```html
<!-- Try these different paths if one doesn't work -->
<link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css"> <!-- Same directory -->
<link rel="stylesheet" href="./style.css"> <!-- Explicit same directory -->
<link rel="stylesheet" href="/style.css"> <!-- Root relative -->
```

