Quick Diagnostic

To see what's happening on GitHub Pages, open your browser's developer tools (F12) and check:

1. Is the CSS file loading? (Check Network tab)
2. What styles are being applied to the footer? (Inspect element)
3. Are there any GitHub Pages default styles overriding yours?

You can also add this temporarily to see what's happening:

```html
<!-- Add this right before the footer for debugging -->
<div style="background: red; color: white; text-align: center; padding: 5px;">
    Debug: Container width = <span id="debug-width"></span>
</div>
<script>
    document.getElementById('debug-width').textContent = 
        document.querySelector('.container').offsetWidth + 'px';
</script>
```

The most likely issue is that GitHub Pages is applying some base styles or the CSS isn't loading with the correct MIME type. The !important flags in the fixed CSS should override any GitHub Pages defaults!
